<h2>HVAC Systems for Boston</h2>
<p>Boston's cold climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of maintaining comfort during harsh winters while remaining efficient during humid summers. Heat pumps with cold-climate capabilities are increasingly popular, with models rated for operation down to -15¬∞F proving effective for most Boston winters. For optimal performance, look for systems with SEER ratings of 16+ for cooling efficiency and HSPF ratings of 9+ for heating efficiency. Dual-fuel systems combining heat pumps with gas furnace backup provide excellent reliability during extreme cold snaps.</p>

