<p>Boston residents benefit from multiple layers of solar and HVAC incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal Investment Tax Credit provides 30% of total system costs through 2032, stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Massachusetts offers the SMART program, providing performance-based incentives of approximately \$0.30-0.40 per kWh produced over 10 years, depending on system size and location factors.</p>

<p>Eversource provides additional rebates for energy-efficient HVAC equipment, including up to \$500 for high-efficiency heat pumps and \$300 for ENERGY STAR central air systems. The Mass Save program offers comprehensive home energy assessments, rebates for insulation and air sealing, and 0% financing for qualified improvements. Solar Renewable Energy Certificates (SRECs) provide ongoing income of \$200-300 annually per 6kW system. Combined, these incentives can reduce total project costs by 40-60%, making clean energy upgrades highly attractive for Boston homeowners.</p>

