<p>South End and North End neighborhoods offer excellent solar potential with their consistent row house orientations, while areas like Cambridge and Somerville adjacent to Boston proper feature larger single-family homes with ample roof space for substantial solar arrays. Dorchester and Roxbury present opportunities for solar adoption in more affordable housing stock, where utility savings have greater impact on household budgets. Waterfront areas like the Seaport benefit from reduced shading but face salt air considerations requiring marine-grade equipment coatings. Each neighborhood's tree coverage, building density, and architectural constraints influence optimal system sizing and equipment selection.</p>

